description: Let n be an even integer > 2. Let PrimeP be the number of prime partition pairs {p,q} corresponding to n such that n = p + q, p and q are prime and p <= q. Let CompP be the number of composite partition pairs {r,s} corresponding to n such that n = r + s, r is prime, s is composite and r <= s. For what n's is 2*PrimeP > CompP?
